      "title": "Concept of System",
      "text": "If you remember that the concept of system is defined by a difference from the environment, by [[Operational Closure]], that is, by indifference to the environment, then system rationality means undoing that, undoing indifference, indifference – what happens in the environment doesn't happen to us – and reinforcing irritability, sensitivity or resonance, whatever those terms are, in the system. This is a paradoxical or, if you will, utopian movement that means excluding the environment and including it again."
